  <!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE -->
  <section class="local-section" id="local">
    <h2>Chimney Sweeping in Pakenham</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Pakenham is the major outer south-eastern growth centre at the end of the metropolitan rail line, a suburb that has transformed from a small Cardinia plains service town into one of Melbourne's fastest-growing residential areas over the past two decades. The housing stock reflects this growth story: the older streets around the Pakenham town centre contain homes from the 1960s through the 1980s with traditional open fireplaces, while the vast residential estates that have expanded west and south from the town core since the 1990s are dominated by large four and five bedroom homes where slow combustion wood heaters were specified as the primary supplementary heating system. These newer estate homes sit on the exposed Cardinia plain, where cold air pushes across flat open farmland in winter and temperatures at the outer edge of the metropolitan area can fall noticeably lower than inner suburbs. The combination of genuine winter cold and a large installed base of slow combustion heaters across the newer estates makes Pakenham one of the highest-demand outer south-eastern suburbs for chimney and flue cleaning. Many of these heaters were installed new and have been in use for a decade or more without a professional service, making the annual clean both a safety and a performance issue. We service Pakenham and the Cardinia corridor regularly.</p></div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS -->
