      <li>Poor draw — the heater won't come to temperature even with the air fully open</li>
      <li>A smoky smell that lingers in the home after the heater is shut down</li>
      <li>Creosote or tar deposits visible around the heater door, flue collar or ceiling plate</li>
      <li>A heater installed several years ago that has never had a professional flue clean</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

